COMPARISON SHOTGUN - METABARCODING

2025-04-03

This scripts present the different steps used for the comparison between shotgun and metabarcoding data in the paper Comparison of metabarcoding and shotgun sequencing confirms the relevance of chloroplastic barcodes for lake phytoplankton diversity assessment (Lemonnier et al., in prep)

METABARCODING DATA

Keep only ASV assigned to phytoplankton
library(data.table)
library(dplyr)
library(stringr)

# Exemple on 23S

# Load the taxonomy tables (output from DADA2 pipeline)
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool <- as.data.frame(readRDS("Results/Metabarcoding/DADA2_ASV_taxa_Phytool_OLA_23S.rds"))
colnames(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool) <- gsub("tax.","", colnames(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool))
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA <- as.data.frame(readRDS("Results/Metabarcoding/DADA2_ASV_taxa_SILVA_OLA_23S.rds"))
colnames(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA) <- gsub("tax.","", colnames(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA))


# Add a seqid column to make the link between the 2 taxonomy tables
ASV_table_23S <- as.data.frame(t(readRDS("Results/Metabarcoding/seqtab_nochim_23S.rds")))
ASV_table_23S <- ASV_table_23S %>% mutate(sequence = 1:n())
ASV_table_23S$sequence <- paste(">seq", sep="", ASV_table_23S$sequence)
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool$seqid <- ASV_table_23S[match(rownames(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool), rownames(ASV_table_23S)),"sequence"]
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool$seqid <- gsub(">","", ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool$seqid)
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA$seqid <- ASV_table_23S[match(rownames(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA), rownames(ASV_table_23S)),"sequence"]
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA$seqid <- gsub(">","", ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA$seqid)

# Keep only assignation with bootstraps values above 80 for SILVA
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA <- subset(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA, boot.Phylum >= 80)

# Combine the 2 tables
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool$phylum_SILVA <- ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA[match(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool$seqid, ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA$seqid),"Phylum"]
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool$boot_SILVA <- ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA[match(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool$seqid, ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_SILVA$seqid),"boot.Phylum"]

# Remove unknown or non-phytoplankton taxa 
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool <- subset(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool, phylum_SILVA == "Cyanobacteria")
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool[is.na(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool$Phylum),"Phylum"] <- "Unknown"
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool <- subset(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool, !Phylum=="Tracheophyta")
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool <- subset(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool, !Phylum=="Rhodophyta")

ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S <- ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_Phytool

# Put NA if bootstrap is under 80
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S[ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$boot.Class < 80, c("Class","Order","Family","Genus","Species")] <- NA
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S[ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$boot.Order < 80, c("Order","Family","Genus","Species")] <- NA
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S[ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$boot.Family < 80, c("Family","Genus","Species")] <- NA
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S[ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$boot.Genus < 80, c("Genus","Species")] <- NA
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$taxa <- paste(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$Phylum,ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$Class,ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$Order,ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$Family,ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$Genus,ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$Species, sep="_")


# Save the taxonomy table
saveRDS(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S, file="Results/Metabarcoding/ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_combined_23S.rds")
Filter ASV table based on taxonomy and create table of relative abundance
# prepare matrix count
ASV_table <- as.data.frame(t(readRDS("Results/Metabarcoding/seqtab_nochim_23S.rds")))
ASV_table <- ASV_table %>% mutate(sequence = 1:n())
ASV_table$sequence <- paste("seq", sep="", ASV_table$sequence)
rownames(ASV_table) <- ASV_table$sequence
ASV_table <- ASV_table[,-36]
colnames(ASV_table) <- gsub('_(.*)_\\w+', '', colnames(ASV_table))

# Remove unwanted taxa from ASV table
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S <- readRDS(file="Results/Metabarcoding/ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_combined_23S.rds")

ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$seq_phylum <- paste(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$seqid,ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$Phylum, sep="_")

# Keep main phylum 
Taxo_23S_subset <- subset(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S,  Phylum=="Bacillariophyta" | Phylum=="Cryptophyta" | Phylum=="Chlorophyta"| Phylum=="Ochrophyta" | Phylum=="Haptophyta"| Phylum=="Cyanobacteria")

ASV_table <- ASV_table[rownames(ASV_table) %in% Taxo_23S_subset$seqid,colnames(ASV_table) %in% rownames(metadata)]
metadata <- metadata[rownames(metadata) %in% colnames(ASV_table),]
ASV_table_23S <- ASV_table


# Create a table of relatie abundance
genre_table <- as.matrix(ASV_table_23S)

s_num<-dim(genre_table)[2]
otu.perc<-matrix(rep("NA",times=(dim(genre_table)[1]*s_num)),nrow=dim(genre_table)[1],ncol=s_num)
rownames(otu.perc)<-rownames(genre_table)
colnames(otu.perc)=colnames(genre_table) 
totals<-colSums(genre_table)

for(s in c(1:s_num)){
  vec<-(genre_table[,s]/totals[s])*100
  otu.perc[,s]<-vec
  rm(vec)
}

write.table(otu.perc, "Results/Metabarcoding/ASV_perc_23S.txt")
Prepare table for comparison
# Load metadata
metadata <- read.table("Results/Metadata/metadata_OLA.csv", header=T, row.names=1, sep=";")

# Load ASV relative abundance table
ASV_table_23S_perc <- as.data.frame(read.table("ASV_perc_23S.txt", header=T, row.names=1))

# Add phylum info
table_23S <- ASV_table_23S
table_23S$phylum <- ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S[match(rownames(table_23S), ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$seqid),"Phylum"]

# Keep main phyla
table_23S_sub <- subset(table_23S, phylum=="Bacillariophyta" | phylum=="Cryptophyta" | phylum=="Chlorophyta"| phylum=="Ochrophyta" |phylum=="Haptophyta"| phylum=="Cyanobacteria")

# Add metadata info
table_23S_sub$lake <- metadata[match(table_23S_sub$variable, rownames(metadata)),"Lac"]
table_23S_sub$Date <- metadata[match(table_23S_sub$variable, rownames(metadata)),"Date"]

# Create table of relative abundance
d23SM <- as.data.frame(table_23S_sub) %>%
  group_by(lake, Date, phylum) %>%
  summarise(shotgun23S = sum(value)) %>%
  group_by(lake, Date,) %>%
  mutate(shotgun23S = round(shotgun23S / sum(shotgun23S)*100, 3)) 

# Add ID for each sample-phylum
d23SM$sample <- metadata[match(d23SM$Date, metadata$Date),"sampleID"]
d23SM$ID <- paste0(d23SM$phylum, d23SM$lake, d23SM$Date, sep="|")
d23SM <- as.data.frame(d23SM)

SHOTGUN DATA

Phytool_23S_good <- readRDS("Results/SortMeRNA/Final_tables/LSU_Phytool_23S_all_samples_good.RDS")
table_23S <- as.data.frame(Phytool_23S_good)

# Add metadata info
table_23S$lake <- metadata[match(table_23S$sample.x, metadata$sampleID),"Lac"]
table_23S$Date <- metadata[match(table_23S$sample.x, metadata$sampleID),"Date"]

# Keep main phyla
table_23S_sub <- subset(table_23S, phylum.x=="Bacillariophyta" | phylum.x=="Cryptophyta" | phylum.x=="Chlorophyta"| phylum.x=="Ochrophyta" | phylum.x=="Haptophyta"| phylum.x=="Cyanobacteria")

# Create table of relative abundance
table_23S_sub$nseq <- 1
d23S <- as.data.frame(table_23S_sub) %>%
  group_by(lake, Date, phylum.x) %>%
  summarise(shotgun23S = sum(nseq)) %>%
  group_by(lake, Date,) %>%
  mutate(shotgun23S = round(shotgun23S / sum(shotgun23S)*100, 3)) 

colnames(d23S) <- c("lake","Date","phylum","shotgun23S")

# Add ID for each sample-phylum
d23S$ID <- paste0(d23S$phylum, d23S$lake, d23S$Date, sep="|")
d23S <- as.data.frame(d23S)

COMPARISON SHOTGUN/METABARCODING FOR EACH PHYLA

# Combine tables
d23S$metabarcoding23S <- d23SM[match(d23S$ID, d23SM$ID),"shotgun23S"]
d23S[is.na(d23S$metabarcoding23S),"metabarcoding23S"] <- 0
d23S$metabarcoding16S <- d16SM[match(d23S$ID, d16SM$ID),"shotgun16S"]
d23S[is.na(d23S$metabarcoding16S),"metabarcoding16S"] <- 0
d23S$shotgun16S <- d16S[match(d23S$ID, d16S$ID),"shotgun16S"]
d23S[is.na(d23S$shotgun16S),"shotgun16S"] <- 0

# Melt table 
md23S <- melt(d23S, id.vars=c("lake","Date","phylum","ID","shotgun23S"))
md23S$variable <- factor(md23S$variable, levels=c("shotgun23S","metabarcoding23S","metabarcoding16S"))
md23S <- na.omit(md23S)

# Keep only dominant phylum
md23S_sub <- subset(md23S, phylum=="Bacillariophyta" | phylum=="Cryptophyta" | phylum=="Chlorophyta"| phylum=="Ochrophyta" | phylum=="Haptophyta"| phylum=="Cyanobacteria")

# Plot
gg <- ggplot(md23S_sub, aes(x=shotgun23S, y=value)) +
      geom_point(aes(fill=variable), shape=21) +
      facet_grid(.~phylum, scales="free") +
      scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0, 0), limits = c(0, 100)) +
      scale_y_continuous(expand = c(0, 0), limits = c(0, 100)) +
      geom_smooth(method="lm", aes(color=variable)) +
      geom_abline(slope = 1, intercept=0) +
      scale_fill_manual(values=c("#e1a95f","#2f4f4f")) +
      scale_color_manual(values=c("#e1a95f","#2f4f4f")) +
      xlab("Shotgun relative abundance (%)") +
      ylab("Metabarcoding relative abundance (%)") +
      theme_bw()
